  "response_text": "The commercial opens in a warmly lit dining room during a children’s birthday party. Several young children sit around a table covered with plates and clear glasses of red drink. In the center is a decorated birthday cake with a small lit candle, and pink balloons float in the background near a bright window with shutters. A little child with curly blond hair leans close to the cake, facing the candle, while a girl with pigtails sits beside them. Suddenly, as the children react and raise their hands, a burst of tiny cake crumbs, sprinkles, or party debris showers upward and rains down over the curly-haired child’s head and the tabletop. The cake remains in the middle, but the area around it looks messy, with particles falling through the warm light.\n\nThe scene changes to a close view of a wooden floor under a chair. Small pale crumbs are scattered across the floorboards near a white chair leg. A dark, handheld cordless vacuum with a narrow nozzle is lowered toward the mess. The nozzle glides over the crumbs, drawing them up from the floor in a small, controlled path, reaching close to the chair leg where a larger vacuum would be awkward.\n\nA small tan puppy appears next, standing in a softly lit room. It walks toward a blue food bowl placed on a black-and-white checkered kitchen floor. The bowl is heaped with dry dog food, and some pieces spill over the rim. The puppy lies down and begins eating near the bowl. In a closer view, the dry food is piled high, then spills down over the side, creating a scatter of kibble on the floor.\n\nA dark DustBuster-style vacuum is shown hanging vertically on a wall-mounted charging bracket. A hand in a coral or pink sleeve reaches in and lifts the compact vacuum away from the holder. Back on the checkered kitchen floor, an adult woman in a loose coral top kneels beside the puppy. She pets the puppy with one hand while holding the cordless vacuum in the other. The puppy keeps eating from the blue bowl, and the woman brings the vacuum nozzle to the spilled kibble, cleaning the small pile beside the bowl without disturbing the dog.\n\nThe setting then shifts to a bright kitchen or dining area with a baby seated in a high chair. The baby, with very light blond hair, wears a teal shirt under light overalls and smiles happily. On the high-chair tray is a small blue cup filled with snack pieces. A closer view shows the cup full of finger-sized snacks. Some of the snacks are later scattered on the floor nearby.\n\nA woman with dark hair pulled back, wearing a white-and-dark striped top and dark pants, crouches on the floor beside the high chair. The baby remains seated to the right, watching from the tray area. The woman uses the same dark handheld vacuum to pick up the scattered snack pieces from the pale floor. She guides the nozzle along the floor in short passes, collecting the small bits near a chair leg and beneath the high chair. As the mess disappears, she looks up toward the baby and smiles.\n\nAt the end, the vacuum is returned to its wall-mounted holder. The dark, tapered body of the handheld cleaner hangs neatly against a light wall, with the product name visible on the front. Large on-screen text appears across the bottom reading “BLACK & DECKER,” accompanied by the brand’s geometric logo, while a hand steadies the vacuum on the charging bracket.",
